docs.lead_paragraph: The R. M. steamship Europa, from Liverpool on the 8th inst., with three days' later European advices, in now about due at this port. Nothing had been seen of her at Sandy Hook at 2 'o clock this morning. Nothing of special importance occurred in Congress yesterday. In the Senate the Invalid Pension bill was passed.

headline.main: ACADEMY OF MEDICINE.; Report of Drs. Beale and Mott as to the Cause of Mr. Whitney's Death-Prolonged Debate--The Subject Laid on the Table-Election of Officers.

docs.lead_paragraph: A special meeting of the Academy of Medicine was held last night in the small chapel of the University for the purpose of completing the election of officers for the current year, and the year next succeeding, there having been a failure at the previous meeting to elect the entire list by three Vice-Presidents, one member of the Committee on Ethics, two members of the Committee on Education, and one Trustee.

docs.snippet: Commissioner BOWNE has sent in the resignation of his office as Quarantine Commissioner, and it is rumored that Mr. HALL'S resignation has also been sent up, but it has not yet been received at the Governor's room.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE YELLOW FEVER CASE--ARREST OF THE CAPTAIN FOR RUNNING QUARANTINE.--The Schooner Hiram E. Bishop, Captain Booth, of Greenport, L. I., which arrived here from Matanzas on Sunday, lost one of the crew--GEORGE SEELEY of Greenport by yellow fever, which he contracted at Matanzas.
